ENTRY            M0380   20260118   20260226   20260226       M143
SUBENT        M0380001   20260118   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                 14         36
TITLE      Fission induced in Ta-nat, W-nat, and Pt-nat targets
            by 69 MeV monochromatic photons
AUTHOR     (O.A.P.Tavares,J.B.Martins,E.De Paiva,E.L.Moreira,
           J.L.Vieira,M.L.Terranova,M.Capognis,L.Casano,
           A.D'angelo,D.Moricciani,F.Ghio,B.Girolami,B.Babusci)
REFERENCE  (J,JP/G,19,805,1993)
INSTITUTE  (3BZLRIO,2ITYCAS,2ITYFRA)
FACILITY   (ESTRG,2ITYFRA) Electron storage ring ADONE.
INC-SOURCE (MPH) Compton backscattering of laser light by the
            high-energy electrons from storage ring ADONE.
DETECTOR   (TRD) Polycarbonate makrofoil N (Bayer AG) sheets.
METHOD     (FISCT)
SAMPLE     The samples consisted of high-purity tantalum,
            tungsten, and platinum metallic foils.
ANALYSIS   The direct measurements of number of fission
            fragments using the scanning of the MAKROFOL sheets
            by means of conventional optical microscopy.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The total errors are given which are the
           sum of the statistical and systematic uncertainties.
COMMENT    A study of photofission on Ta-nat, W-nat, and Pt-nat
            nuclei induced by monochromatic photons of 69 MeV
            has been performed. The fission yields have been
            measured by using MAKROFOIL sheets as fission-track
            detectors, in thick-target 2Pi geometry. The
            absolute photofission cross sections for the
            tantalum, tungsten, and platinum targets were found
            and the corresponding deduced fissilities were
            obtained as (3.2 (0.7)), (3.4 (08)), and (6.4 (1.3))
            multiplied to 10**(-4).
STATUS     (TABLE,,O.A.P.Tavares+,J,JP/G,19,805,1993)
            Data from Table 2.
HISTORY    (19960223C)
           (19960313U)
           (20100112A) Corrections  of   AUTHOR   -  B.GIROLAMI,
            dates, lowercase, EXP, NODATA for SUBENTS 3, 5, 7.
           (20260118U) Corrected by VV and SD: STATUS.
